==English==

===Etymology===
{{ME.}} ''[[sunnenday]]'' from {{OE.}} ''[[sunnandæg]]'', day of the sun, from ''[[sunne]]'', [[sun]], + ''[[dæg]]'', [[day]], as a translation of {{L.}} ''[[dies solis]]''; declared the "venerable day of the sun" by Roman Emperor [[w:Constantine|Constantine]] on March 7, AD 321

